07209nam a22011535i 9781783099054DE-B159720220424125308.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220424t20172017enk    fo  d z      eng d  a97817830990547 a10.21832/97817830990542doi  a(DE-B1597)491609  a(OCoLC)1076464001  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aenkcGB-BST 4aP115.2b.H47 2018 7aLAN0090402bisacsh04a372.6223  aER 930qBVB2rvk0(DE-625)rvk/27776:00aHeritage and School Language Literacy Development in Migrant Children :bInterdependence or Independence? /ced. by Raphael Berthele, Amelia Lambelet. 1aBristol ;aBlue Ridge Summit : bMultilingual Matters, c[2017] 4c©2017  a1 online resource  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aSecond Language Acquisition00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tContributors -- t1. Investigating Interdependence and Literacy Development in Heritage Language Speakers: Theoretical and Methodological Considerations -- t2. Testing Interdependence in Portuguese Heritage Speakers in Switzerland: The HELASCOT Project -- t3. On the Sociolinguistic Embedding of Portuguese Heritage Language Speakers in Switzerland: Socio-Economic Status and Home Literacy Environment (HELASCOT Project) -- t4. Reading Comprehension Development in Portuguese Heritage Speakers in Switzerland (HELASCOT Project) -- t5. The Deve lopment of Argumentative and Narrative Writing Skills in Portuguese Heritage Speakers in Switzerland (HELASCOT Project) -- t6. Testing the Interdependence of Languages (HELASCOT Project) -- t7. Language Skill Transfer Effects: Moving from Heritage Language to School Language in Kindergarten -- t8. Promoting Multilingualism Through Heritage Language Courses: New Perspectives on the Transfer Effect -- t9. The Development of Russian Heritage Pupils’ Writing Profi ciency in Finnish and Russian -- t10. Assessing Heritage Languages and Interdependence: Why and How? -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis book discusses literacy development in heritage language speakers and presents the results of four different quantitative studies that investigate the transfer of literacy skills in bi- and multilingual language development. The empirical studies focus on different populations of pupils, most of them located in various parts of Switzerland, and emphasise the potential residing in shared or transferred resources between their heritage languages and the languages spoken in the region to which their family has immigrated. The goal of all studies was to gain an understanding of the factors, both linguistic and non-linguistic in nature, that contribute to the development of language skills in both the heritage and school languages. Theoretical assumptions are put to the test via hypothesis testing and the generally shared assumptions on bilingual education are questioned based on the data. Furthermore, methodological problems in the investigation of linguistic interdependence are discussed. This book contributes to the scholarly investigation of potential beneficial effects in academic proficiency across languages in migrant children.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aCode switching (Linguistics). 0aEducation, Bilingual. 0aHeritage language speakersxEducation. 0aImmigrant childrenxEducation. 0aInterlanguage (Language learning). 0aLanguage and languagesxStudy and teaching. 0aMultilingual education. 0aMultilingualism in children. 0aSociolinguistics. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Psycholinguistics.2bisacsh  aSLA.  abilingual education.  abilingualism.  abiliteracy.  acrosslinguistic influence.  aheritage language learning.  aheritage language maintenance.  aheritage language students.  aheritage language.  aint